cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

This paper addresses the problem of reducing energy consumption in deep neural networks, which is a common concern in computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper proposes a novel approach for joint quantization of weights and activations, which is a technique commonly used in neural network optimization (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the hardware costs of the proposed approach, which is relevant to computer architecture (cs.AR).
